725719f-a.title: Queens: 93rd Avenue - 172nd Street
725719f-a.text:
93rd Avenue, north side, east from 172nd to 173rd Streets.
The first two dwellings were owned by Mrs. L. Waters in 1873;
the farthest one, where automobile is parked, by J. McDonald.
The avenue at this point was then named Willow Street.
P. L. Sperr  Apri 1, 1932
